Azimio la Umoja One Kenya
Alliance party leader Raila Odinga has commended the Directorate of Immigration
Services for streamlining its passport renewal services. In a tweet on Thursday, Raila noted that he
was accorded fast and convenient services at the Immigration DepartmentÂ when he went to Nyayo House to renew his expired passport. "My passport expired and
today I went down to the immigration department to renew it. I'd like to thank
the agency's friendly and helpful staff for the reception and timely service," read the tweet accompanied by pictures of the former premier walking around the
department's headquarters.  Raila was received by
Immigration and Citizen Services Principal Secretary (PS) Julius Bitok who gave
him a brief tour of the facility before the Azimio frontman renewed his passport. 